South Africa will move from Level 3 to Level 2 lockdown effectively from midnight on Monday. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced government’s risk-adjusted strategy on the coronavirus pandemic in the country on Saturday evening. A curfew of 10pm – 4am will still be in place, and restrictions of no more than 50 people at funerals and gatherings will still need to be adhered to. Interprovincial travel will be allowed under level two lockdown; while domestic air travel will also be permitted. The Infographic below provides a comprehensive outline of sectors permitted under Level 2 lockdown: sabcnews.com | SABC News channel | SABC Radio news SA COVID-19 LOCKDOWN LEVEL 2 TRANSPORT RESTRICTIONS Domestic air travel restored. Car rental services restored. Movement between provinces at Level 1 and 2 restrictions. MOVEMENT RESTRICTIONS SECTORS PERMITTED Moderate virus spread, with moderate ﻿readiness Source: South African government All  retail Construction LEVEL 2 All other manufacturing Mining  All mines at 100% capacity All government services Installation Repairs Maintenance Domestic work and cleaningservices Informal waste pickers RETAIL LEVEL 2 LEVEL 2 RENTAL (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); The President also announced the lifting on the ban of alcohol and tobacco sales. Gyms and accommodation services can also reopen under strict health protocols. Visits to family and friends in small groups will also be allowed, as seen in the graphic below: sabcnews.com | SABC News Channel | SABC Radio news LOCKDOWN LEVEL 2 What You Need To Know Restaurants may remain open, ﻿with a curfew between 10pm and 4am Alcohol maybe served in all licensed restaurants Visits to family and friends are permitted in small groups Hotel and acco